Skin lesion classification using a CNN model¶

In this part we train a classification convolutional model on our dataset. To address the small dataset issue, we finetune an already pretrained network (an Inception V3 Network) and we use data augmentation. Freezing the top of the model and the last convolutinnal layer, we end up with 2.149.000 trainable weights. Finally our model achieves a 0.73 score. This score might be improved by adding more trainable weights or using ensemble models.

def display_data(dataset):

  items = dataset.take(1)

  fig, axs = plt.subplots(4, 4, figsize=(15,15))

  for data in items:
    for i in range(4):
      for j in range(4):
        axs[i, j].imshow((data[0][(i + 4*j)].numpy()*255.).astype('uint8'))
        axs[i, j].set_title(str(data[1][i + 4*j].numpy()))
        axs[i, j].axis('off')

  plt.show()

Model definition and training¶

In [91]:
from tensorflow.keras.applications import VGG16, InceptionV3

backbones = [
             VGG16,
             InceptionV3
]

def get_model(back):
  backbone = back(include_top=True, input_shape=(299,299,3))

  for layer in backbone.layers:
    if layer.name in ['predictions', 'batch_normalization_1221', 'batch_normalization_1213' , 'conv2d_1221']:
      layer.trainable = True
    else:
      layer.trainable = False

  input = tf.keras.layers.Input((299,299,3))
  x = backbone(input)
  x = tf.keras.layers.Flatten()(x)
  x = tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.3)(x)
  x = tf.keras.layers.Dense(100, activation='relu')(x)
  x = tf.keras.layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)

  model = tf.keras.Model(input, x)

  return(model)

Model evaluation¶

The model is only evaluated on the validation set. Using an additionnal testing dataset is required to conclude properly.

In [97]:
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve

predictions = np.array([])
labels =  np.array([])
for x, y in val_ds:
  predictions = np.concatenate([predictions, model.predict(x).ravel()])
  labels = np.concatenate([labels, y.numpy()])

y_pred_keras = model.predict(val_ds).ravel()
fp, tp, thresholds_keras = roc_curve(labels, predictions)
